      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's understandable why you feel suspicious given the neighbor's Wi-Fi name, but it is highly unlikely they are tracking your exact location using signal strength surges. Wi-Fi signal strength changes are often normal due to walls, appliances, or router positioning within your own home. If you are concerned about privacy, the best course of action is simply to ensure your own home network uses a strong, non-identifying password.",
